lead_paragraph: About the first business before the Legislature of Kentucky, at its approaching session, is the choice of an occupant for the seat now filled by, Judge Underwood, in the U. S. Senate. Among the most prominent names suggested for the position, are those of Mr. Underwood, and Hon. George Robertson, of Lexington.
